com.orange.api.rfid.capture.application.server Orange RFID System - EPC application [Module epcis_application-server] Capture and Access WS implementations
Include AccessImpl for accessing EPCIS data, AccessPsionImpl for simpler functions for mobile readers, and CaptureImpl for receiving ECReports and sending them to appropriate ActionInterface class (depending on configuration read in BPESpec file).
com.orange.api.rfid.capture.application.server.businessapps Orange RFID System - EPC application [Module epcis_application-server] Generic GUIs for handling business processes
Include BPEventGui for uploading BPEventType XML files, and GenericTransactionGui for processing (i.e., starting and stopping manually) business steps that would call CaptureImpl web service.
com.orange.api.rfid.capture.application.server.command Orange RFID System - EPC application [Module epcis_application-server] Where the intelligence is: classes crossing ECReports and BPEventType into EPCISEvent
Abstract class is ActionAbstract
com.orange.api.rfid.capture.application.server.configure Orange RFID System - EPC application [Module epcis_application-server] Configuration WS implementations
Mainly include ConfigureImpl for setting/getting parameters, vocabularies (VocabularyType) and business process events (BPEventType), as well as ConfigurePsionImpl for simpler functions for mobile readers

This overview shows all the packages that are included in the OrangeRfidEpc Maven project; for more details and global architecture, see description hereafter.


RFID Box and EPCglobal architecture

Five main components here:

  • Readers, printers and GPIOs: components especially include
    • Psion WorkAbout Pro (mobile reader) applications, written in C# (out of Maven build)
    • Tagsys SRU 400 (tablet reader) applications: see com.orange.api.rfid.capture.tagsys.registrationstation for processing data from Tagsys Registration Station application.
    • Specific GPIOs from IER or Tagsys
  • RFID Box:
    • EPCglobal's ALE layer in fc-commons and fc-server modules: start with com.orange.api.rfid.ale.server.subscriber package
      Note: ALE layers is based on Fosstrak's ALE (see org.fosstrak.ale.server)
    • EPCglobal's Capture and query layer in epcis_application-commons and epcis-application-server modules: start with com.orange.api.rfid.capture.application.server package
    • RFID Box's GUI in epc-webclient modules: start with com.orange.api.rfid.ui.box.client packages
  • EPCIS:
    • EPCglobal's EPCIS layer, using Fosstrak's EPCIS repository (see org.fosstrak.epcis.repository) with possible access control extension (see access_control.filter)
    • EPCIS console: see for instance com.orange.api.ons package.
    • Reporting: see com.orange.api.rfid.report.client package.
  • EPCIS subscribing applications: start with com.orange.api.epcis.subscriber.receiver package or look at com.orange.api.epcis.jms package.
  • Provisioning portal: start with com.orange.epcglobal.portal.client package
  • Testing and validation tools:
  • Demonstrations and fixed web sites
  • plus additional components like commons library or external JARs from Fosstrak.
